body:
Hi! I'm getting error when try to implement extern function that returns parametrized class:

```
%Error: test.sv:12:5: Assign RHS expects a CLASSREFDTYPE 'value_cls', got CLASSREFDTYPE 'value_cls__Tz1'
                    : ... note: In instance 'test'
   12 |     return obj;
      |     ^~~~~~
%Error: test.sv:16:50: Assign RHS expects a CLASSREFDTYPE 'value_cls__Tz1', got CLASSREFDTYPE 'value_cls'
                     : ... note: In instance 'test'
   16 |     value_cls#(string) foo = value_cls#(string)::create("foo");
      |                                                  ^~~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 2 error(s)
```

<details>
  <summary>test.sv</summary>

```verilog
module test;

  class value_cls#(type VALUE_T=int unsigned);
    VALUE_T value;

    extern static function value_cls#(VALUE_T) create(VALUE_T value);
  endclass : value_cls

  function value_cls value_cls::create(VALUE_T value);
    value_cls#(VALUE_T) obj = new();
    obj.value = value;
    return obj;
  endfunction : create

  initial begin
    value_cls#(string) foo = value_cls#(string)::create("foo");
    $display(foo.value);
    $finish();
  end

endmodule
```
</details>

Reproducer:

```bash
verilator --binary test.sv && ./obj_dir/Vtest
```

Code seems legit and works in some commercial simmulators.

Verilator version: Verilator 5.022 2024-02-24 rev v5.020-157-g2b4852048
OS: Ubuntu 22.04.4 LTS
